"script": "Deep inside Neptune and Uranus, it might literally rain diamonds. Here's how. These planets are stuffed with methane, a gas made of carbon and hydrogen. As you sink toward their cores, the pressure becomes unimaginable, millions of times stronger than the air on Earth. That crushing force rips the methane apart and squeezes the leftover carbon until it locks into solid diamond. Then those diamonds, some possibly the size of icebergs, sink slowly through thousands of miles of hot slush toward the center. So somewhere out there, two planets are raining a treasure no one will ever hold.",
